The article is a viewer's guide to the State of the Union address given by President Obama in 2010. It highlights the key points and proposals made by the President in his speech. These include recovering money spent on bank bailouts, supporting small businesses, investing in infrastructure, creating clean energy jobs, increasing exports, improving education, making college more affordable, helping middle-class families, addressing the housing crisis, reforming lobbying and campaign finance, countering the Citizens United decision, supporting military families, and addressing national security issues such as nuclear proliferation and bioterrorism. The President also expressed his commitment to repealing "Don't Ask, Don't Tell," and to immigration reform.